# Dashboard Pages — Server-First

Every dashboard page MUST be a Server Component that fetches data at the top level.

## Pattern

```tsx
// page.tsx — Server Component (NO 'use client')
import { getCurrentUser } from '@/lib/auth';
import { prisma } from '@/lib/prisma';
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';
import ClientPart from './ClientPart';

export default async function Page() {
  const user = await getCurrentUser();
  if (!user) redirect('/login');
  const tenantId = user.memberships[0].tenantId;

  const data = await prisma.xxx.findMany({ where: { tenantId } });
  return <ClientPart data={data} />;
}
```

## Rules

- **NEVER** use `useEffect` to fetch data on page load
- **NEVER** show "טוען..." loading spinners for initial page data
- Pass all data as props to client components
- Client components handle forms, filters, modals — NOT data fetching
- Use `searchParams` for server-side filtering (not client state)
